                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14193377" author="jahewson" created="Sat, 1 Nov 2014 19:18:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;So I took a look at this file and it isn&apos;t a font bug. The width for character 60 in the FontDescriptor is 0 and in the embedded font it is 633. So the file really does contain this.&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;What I don&apos;t know is what PDF/A actually requires of the font in order to be valid, it&apos;s obviously not the same as what PDFBox&apos;s Preflight is doing, but without a copy of the PDF/A spec, I can&apos;t say. Does anybody know?&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14193844" author="msahyoun" created="Sun, 2 Nov 2014 14:22:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AFAIU character 60 is /negationslash which does have a width of 0 in the font program. If I&#8217;m mistaken maybe you could let me know which character 60 is with it&#8217;s name.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14193970" author="jahewson" created="Sun, 2 Nov 2014 19:22:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, you&apos;re right, the width in the charstring is -770 which is subtracted from the NominalWidth of 770 giving a width of 0. That means that there &lt;em&gt;is&lt;/em&gt; a bug in our CFF or charstring handling.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14193975" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 2 Nov 2014 19:35:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1636172 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1636172&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1636172&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2442&quot; title=&quot;false negative? 3.1.6 : Invalid Font definition, Width (633.0) of the character &amp;quot;60&amp;quot; in the font program &amp;quot;BNGLNN+LucidaMath-Symbol&amp;quot; is inconsistent with the width (0.0) in the PDF dictionary.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2442&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2442&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Don&apos;t use DefaultWidth for zero-width characters&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14193976" author="jahewson" created="Sun, 2 Nov 2014 19:35:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Found it: there was a bug with the handling of DefaultWidth for Type 2 Charstrings. Thanks Maruan.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
